premise_source_doc_sentence: Films advertised as Disney Digital 3-D come from a number of sources , film , digital camera as well as animation software , and can be presented using any digital 3D technology , including RealD , Dolby 3D , XpanD 3D and MasterImage 3D .

Disney Digital 3-D is a brand name used by The Walt Disney Company to describe three-dimensional films made and released by Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures mostly under the Walt Disney Pictures label and shown exclusively using digital projection .
Now there are several competing digital 3D formats including Dolby 3D , XpanD 3D , Panavision 3D , MasterImage 3D and IMAX 3D .

Step Up 3D premiered in Hollywood at the El Capitan Theater on August 2 , 2010 and was subsequently released worldwide on August 6 , 2010 , through conventional 2D and 3D  (  in RealD 3D , Dolby 3D , and XpanD 3D  )  formats .
The film has been released in RealD 3D , XpanD 3D , and Dolby 3D with Max Giwa and Dania Pasquini returning to direct .
